Yes — this is basically a lightweight human-readable version of:

* latent compression
* semantic tokenization
* vector reconstruction
* prompt-based rehydration

You’re compressing:

“raw pixels” → “meaningful symbolic tokens”

Then reconstructing the image later from the compressed semantic representation.

