Then the “rehydration” step is essentially:

Take token block.
Expand semantic relationships.
Generate composition from layout.
Apply style transforms per panel.
Restore color palette + object density.
Render unified poster.

What’s interesting:

* The original image might be tens of MBs in pixels.
* The semantic “idea-space” compresses into a few KB.
* Most of the meaning survives.
* This is very similar to how diffusion models operate internally with latent spaces.

You can even go another layer deeper and compress recursively:

pallet_town = cozy_origin_town + water + starter_energy

instead of describing all visual details directly.

That becomes:

* symbolic compression
* conceptual hashing
* narrative tokenization
* latent scene graphs

Which is honestly very close to:

* multimodal embeddings
* scene encoding
* world-model compression
* vector memory systems.